---
const title = "Quantum — taught like you're a working developer";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Quantum computing, taught like you're a working developer. Interactive essays backed by a real in-browser quantum simulator."
    />
  </head>
  <body class="bg-slate-950 text-slate-100 antialiased">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-24">
      <p class="mb-4 text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-indigo-400">
        Phase 2 — the qubit essay is live
      </p>
      <h1 class="mb-6 text-5xl font-semibold leading-tight">
        Quantum computing,<br />taught like you're a working developer.
      </h1>
      <p class="mb-10 text-xl text-slate-300">
        Interactive scrollytelling essays backed by a real, tiny, in-browser
        quantum simulator. No PhD required. No hand-wavy coin-spinning
        analogies.
      </p>

      <section class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/50 p-6 mb-8">
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">
          Read the flagship essay
        </h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4">
          Press gates, drag the Bloch sphere arrow, sweep continuous
          rotation sliders, and pin sticky notes wherever something
          clicks.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/qubit"
          class="inline-block rounded-md bg-indigo-500 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-white hover:bg-indigo-400 focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-indigo-300"
        >
          What is a Qubit? →
        </a>
      </section>

      <section class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/50 p-6">
        <h2 class="mb-3 text-lg font-medium text-slate-100">
          Status
        </h2>
        <ul class="space-y-1 text-slate-400">
          <li>[done] Phase 1 — simulator (X/Y/Z/H/S/T/CNOT/Rx/Ry/Rz + measurement)</li>
          <li>[done] Phase 2 — flagship "What is a Qubit?" essay</li>
          <li>[next] Phase 3 — Quantum Sandbox + creative outputs</li>
          <li>[planned] Phase 4 — full foundations essay track</li>
          <li>[planned] Phase 5 — algorithm track + v1 launch</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
